@Node What
@{b}What's OneTouchMac ?@{ub}

This a simple prog witch allow you to boot with another startup-sequence
by pressing the left mouse bouton or the right mouse button. You can
execute 2 differents startups, depending on witch mouse button you press.
If you press a mouse button, the REAL STARTUP-SEQUENCE Will Stop Loading.

@{b}NOTE THAT THIS PROGRAME ONLY WORK WITH MOUSE CONNECTED TO THE ORIGINAL
AMIGA MOUSE PORT (PORT 1)@{ub}

@EndNode

@Node Why
@{b}Why This name ?@{ub}

I made this little program to boot the MacOS via shapeshifter without
loading the workbench or typing commands after a boot "with no startup-sequence".
So I called it OneTouchMac ! :)

@EndNode

@Node Install
@{b}INSTALATION: VERY IMPORTANT !@{ub}

the install is very easy ! just put OnetouchMac at the very first
Startup-sequence line (before Setpatch, it's better).But YOU MUST
TYPE "FAILAT 1" BEFORE, else OnTouchMac will execute your
startup without stop the real Startup-sequence execution. But
maybe is that you want...

It has been compiled on a A1200 + 060 and KS+WB 3.1
I Think it must run on Any Amiga with WB 2.0+
Please tell if it works or not on your Amiga, thanks !

@EndNode

@Node Usage
@{b}USAGE: ULTRA SIMPLE !!!@{ub}

OneTouchMac <Your startup file 1> [<Your startup file 2>]

Note that your are not expected to type a second startup File. Don't
forget to enter the full path !

@{b}Please, If you use this soft, and if you like it, send me a Mail :)@{ub}

@EndNode

@Node Misc
@{b}MISC@{ub}

Note that Middle Mouse button is not yet supported. But if you
want it to be supported, Email me, I will do it !
I hadn't implemented it 'cause I didn't need it, and I only have
a 2 buttons Mouse so I can't test... :)

@Endnode

